(43, 6, 4, 43, 2, 13, 13, 'the passover, a feast of the Jews', 'Passover References in John', 'Both passages emphasize the proximity of the Passover, indicating its significance in the narrative. The mention of the Passover in both verses connects the events surrounding Jesus'' actions in Jerusalem.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 4, 43, 11, 55, 55, 'the passover, a feast of the Jews', 'Connection of Passover References', 'Both passages emphasize the proximity of the Passover, indicating its significance in the Jewish calendar. The mention of the Passover in both contexts highlights the communal preparations and spiritual significance associated with this feast.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
